The article expresses the deep sorrow and commitment to honoring the memory of the 13 service members who tragically lost their lives in a terrorist attack at Abbey Gate in Afghanistan. It acknowledges the immense sacrifice made by all the U.S. service members who died or were wounded during the two decades of war in Afghanistan. The article also emphasizes the sacred obligation to support and care for service members, veterans, their families, caregivers, and survivors. The author expresses condolences to the families of the fallen warriors and vows to provide ongoing support.